Significant changes made in this fork (macOS port)
--------------------------------------------------
  * Replaced the Windows PowerShell backend (run.ps1's HTTP listener) with a
    Node.js server (server.js) implementing the same local /api/* surface.
  * Added a macOS launcher (run.sh), replacing run.ps1 / run.bat.
  * Run model-issued commands through PowerShell 7 (pwsh) on macOS, with a zsh
    fallback (runtime/pwsh is git-ignored and fetched locally).
  * Added tools/prepare-searxng.sh to build the local SearXNG search engine on
    macOS, replacing the Windows tools/prepare-searxng.ps1.
  * Reworked the web-search endpoint URL handling and added cold-start retry;
    adjusted weather, Google OAuth, file, and proxy endpoints for portable Node.
  * Enabled voice barge-in and a fresh-start-on-manual-disconnect behavior.
  * Re-themed the UI (electric-violet) and renamed the product to "ShadowMac".

Not ported
----------
  * Windows desktop GUI automation (desktop_controller.ps1 — uses the Win32 API).
  * The global push-to-talk hotkey (Windows-only).

The original Windows-specific files (run.ps1, run.bat, desktop_controller.ps1,
installer/, etc.) are retained in this repository for transparency and
attribution to the original project.
